================================================================================
GYMRT2A ENVIRONMENT (marl_mrt2a/env/)
================================================================================

Original implementation by Lucas C. D. Bezerra (2025):
- Multi-robot task allocation grid environment
- Supports agent communication and intention sharing
- CNN-based spatial observation spaces
- Integration with various pathfinding and coordination algorithms
- Support for different task levels and reward structures

Components include:
- marl_mrt2a/env/gymrt2a/ - Complete environment implementation
- Grid-based multi-agent coordination
- Communication and intention sharing mechanisms
- Spatial action interfaces
- Custom rendering and visualization

================================================================================
PCFA ALGORITHM (marl_mrt2a/PCFA/)
================================================================================

Original implementation by Lucas C. D. Bezerra (2025):
- Project Manager-oriented Coalition Formation Algorithm
- Market-based multi-agent task allocation
- Integration with gymrt2a environment
- A* pathfinding integration
- Communication and consensus mechanisms

================================================================================
ANALYSIS AND COMPARISON TOOLS (marl_mrt2a/examples/)
================================================================================

Original implementation by Lucas C. D. Bezerra (2025):
- Comprehensive comparison framework for MARL algorithms
- Integration with Weights & Biases for experiment tracking
- Baseline implementations (PCFA, hardcoded heuristics)
- Performance analysis and visualization tools
- Automated experiment execution and data collection

================================================================================
A* PATHFINDING COMPONENT
================================================================================

The A* pathfinding implementation in marl_mrt2a/env/gymrt2a/astar.py is based on
algorithms from Red Blob Games, licensed under Apache License 2.0.
Original: https://www.redblobgames.com/pathfinding/a-star/
Adapted by Lucas C. D. Bezerra (2025).

